@selarem we already told you about it. The nl_forced_its = 2 was used to force the system to run at least two nonlinear iterations.
I also told you this, with automatic scaling, it is strongly recommended to use nl_rel_tol instead of nl_abs_tol. Depends on your problem, 1e-6 ~ 1e-9 is what I typically use for nl_rel_tol.
Integration typically uses gaussian rule. There is no difference between linear and nonlinear problems.
